%20penalty.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELyft%20has%20agreed%20to%20pay%20a%20%242.1%20million%20civil%20penalty%20as%20part%20of%20a%20proposed%20settlement%20following%20a%20federal%20lawsuit%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice%20filed%20a%20complaint%20against%20Lyft%20on%20Friday%2C%20saying%20the%20rideshare%20company%20violated%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20Act%20between%20April%202021%20and%20June%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20department%20said%20Lyft%20made%20%26quot%3Bdeceptive%20earnings%20claims%26quot%3B%20about%20how%20much%20drivers%20could%20earn%20each%20hour%20%E2%80%94%20and%20in%20special%20incentives%20%E2%80%94%20in%20some%20advertisements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLyft%20used%20the%20hourly%20earnings%20calculation%20at%20the%2080th%20percentile%20for%20a%20given%20region.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20even%20relying%20on%20Lyft's%20own%20calculations%2C%20only%20the%20top%2020%25%20of%20Drivers%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%2C%20only%20one%20in%20five%20Drivers%20%E2%80%94%20earned%20the%20hourly%20earnings%20figures%20quoted%20in%20the%20ads%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20complaint%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20in%20August%202021%2C%20Lyft%20claimed%20that%20Drivers%20in%20New%20Jersey%20could%20earn%20up%20to%20%2434%20per%20hour%20when%20Lyft's%20own%20calculations%20put%20the%20median%20earnings%20at%20only%20%2425%20per%20hour.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Department's%20complaint%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20Lyft%20presented%20the%20earnings%20claim%20as%20an%20hourly%20amount%20and%20did%20not%20disclose%20that%20tips%20were%20factored%20into%20the%20figure%2C%20many%20Drivers%20were%20likely%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20tips%20they%20earned%20would%20be%20additional%20to%20the%20hourly%20earnings%20advertised%20by%20the%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELyft%20also%20shared%20advertisements%20with%20%26quot%3Bearnings%20guarantees%26quot%3B%3C