s.%3Cp%3ERich%20Legg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20friend%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20start%20an%20eCommerce%20company%20on%20a%20%2410%2C000%20budget.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20of%20the%20first%20steps%20we%20took%20was%20selecting%20a%20product%20to%20sell.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20consulting%20experts%20and%20using%20data%20from%20Helium%2010%2C%20we%20chose%20pickleball%20paddles.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20friend%20and%20I%20committed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaunching-an-e-commerce-business-step-one-finding-business-partner-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuilding%20our%20own%20eCommerce%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20our%20first%20task%20was%20selecting%20a%20product%20to%20sell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20knew%20we%20wanted%20to%20create%20something%20of%20our%20own%20(rather%20than%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-money-amazon-retail-arbitrage-strategies-resell-products-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20arbitrage%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20buy%20and%20resell%20an%20existing%20product)%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20was%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20infinitely%20many%20directions%20we%20could%20pursue.%20We%20talked%20in%20circles%20for%20weeks%2C%20plagued%20by%20decision%20fatigue.%20Our%20working%20list%20included%20but%20was%20not%20limited%20to%2C%20kitchen%20sponges%2C%20elbow%20braces%2C%20zip%20ties%2C%20wind-up%20toys%2C%20cookie%20cutters%2C%20and%20even%20seasonal-specific%20items%20like%20holiday%20socks.%20And%20it%20felt%20like%20the%20blind%20leading%20the%20blind%3A%20My%20experience%20with%20eCommerce%20was%20secondhand%2C%20having%20reported%20on%20successful%20Amazon%20sellers.%20My%20business%20partner%20worked%20in%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20spend%20more%20time%20working%20through%20whether%20there%20was%20enough%20demand%20for%20elbow%20braces%20or%20too%20much%20competition%20in%20the%20cookie-cutter%20space%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20ask%20for%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20reached%20out%20to%20Joe%20Reeves%2C%20who%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-sell-on-amazon-succeed-start-side-hustle-ecommerce-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuilding%20his%20own%20eCommerce%20empire%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20co-founded%20the%20consulting%20business%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.330trading.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E330%20Trading%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20people%20do%20exactly%20what%20we%20were%20hoping%20to%20do%3A%20Make%20money%20selling%20things%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20his%20cofounder%2C%20Tyler%20Walter%2C%20agreed%20to%20meet.%20They%20assigned%20us%20homework%20ahead%20of%20the%20call%3A%20Select%20a%20category%20we%20wanted%20to%20sell%20in%20and%20come%20up%20with%20a%20list%20of%20specific%20product%20ideas%20in%20that%20space.%20To%20get%20the%20ideas%20flowing%2C%20they%20encouraged%20us%20to%20think%20about%20our%20hobbies%20and%20how%20we%20generally%20spend%20our%20time.%20%3Cem%3EWhat%20do%20you%20know%20and%20like%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20easy%20question%20to%20answer%3A%20We%20both%20grew%20up%20surrounded%20by%20tennis%20and%20competed%20collegiately.%20Years%20after%20graduating%2C%20we%20still%20played%20recreationally%20and%20spent%20our%20weekends%20teaching.%20We%20dabbled%20in%20other%20racket%20sports%2C%20including%20pickleball%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpadel-vs-pickleball-the-future-of-racket-sports-in-america-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epadel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20paddle%20tennis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20kitchen%20sponges%20or%20zip%20ties%20we%20should%20be%20producing%3B%20it%20was%20something%20racket-sport-related.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20pinpointing%20our%20category%2C%20the%20next%20step%20was%20listing%20spe