t%20savings%2C%20starting%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aa3e47db-cfea-4dbc-85ba-2482e91ab970%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAndrew%20Crowell%2C%20vice%20chairman%20of%20wealth%20management%20at%20D.A.%20Davidson%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Crowell%20and%20other%20experts%2C%20the%20biggest%20piece%20of%20retirement%20advice%20is%20deceptively%20simple%3A%20start%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20even%20just%20a%20modest%20allocation%20to%20investments%2C%20your%20money%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20double%20every%207%20to%2010%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Crowell%20said.%20That%20means%20for%20a%2020-something%20Gen%20Zer%20just%20starting%20their%20career%2C%20their%20money%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20double%20at%20least%20four%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20advantage%20of%20your%20workplace%20retirement%20plan%2C%20such%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20you%20can%20contribute%20a%20portion%20of%20your%20salary%20to%20an%20account.%20Employers%20often%20match%20employee%20contributions%20up%20to%20a%20certain%20percentage%2C%20typically%20between%203%25%20and%206%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20investing%20for%20the%20long%20term%2C%20Crowell%20recommends%20putting%20your%20money%20into%20higher-yielding%20assets%20such%20as%20stocks%20to%20ensure%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigher-long-term-inflation-outlook-investing-strategy-attractive-bonds-stocks-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20erode%20your%20savings.%20The%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20has%20posted%20an%20annualized%20return%20of%2013%25%20in%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20well%20above%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBasic%20budgeting%20strategies%2C%20such%20as%20keeping%20housing%20costs%20at%2030%25%20or%20lower%20of%20your%20total%20paycheck%2C%20can%20also%20create%20a%20strong%20foundation%20for%20retirement%20savings%2C%20Crowell%20said.%20But%20don't%20panic%20if%20rent%20takes%20up%20a%20larger%20proportion%20of%20your%20take-home%20pay%20and%20prevents%20you%20from%20saving%20as%20much%20as%20you'd%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheir%20peak%20earning%20potential%20is%20in%20the%20future%20somewhere%20years%20from%20now%2C%20and%20they're%20finding%20just%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20to%20be%20very%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20Crowell%20said%20of%20Gen%20Zers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20amount%20of%20savings%20is%20too%20small.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20less%20important%20how%20much%20you%20save%20out%20of%20your%20paycheck%20than%20it%20is%20just%20to%20get%20started.%20You%20can%20always%20dial%20it%20up%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20Crowell%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2282328411-a680-4c49-bc2f-60b12971759b%5C%22%3EAyako%20Yoshioka%2C%20senior%20portfolio%20manager%20at%20Wealth%20Enhancement%20Group%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20ways%20to%20save%20for%20retirement%20outside%20a%20traditional%20401(k)%2C%20Yoshioka%20pointed%20out.%20Self-employed%20people%20can%20utilize%20a%20Simplified%20Employee%20Pension%20(SEP)%20IRA%20to%20save%20for%20retirement%20and%20enjoy%20tax-deductible%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-roth-ira%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoth%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20allows%20you%20to%20contribute%20after-tax%20dollars%20for%20retirement%2C%20is%20also%20a%20great%20choice%2C%20Yoshioka%20said.%20Once%20placed%20inside%20a%20Roth%20IRA%2C%20contributions%20and%20earnings%20grow%20tax-free%20and%20can%20typically%20be%20withdrawn%20tax-free%20in%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20like%20to%20pick%20individual%20stocks%20and%20funds%2C%20opening%20a%20brokerage%20account%20and%20building%20your%20own%20portfolio%20is%20another%20way%20to%20invest%20your%20savings.%20But%20for%20those%20who%20do%20trade%20stocks%2C%20Yoshioka%20flags%20that%20there%20are%20capital%20gains%20taxes%20levied%20on%20the%20profits%20of%20an%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20retirement%20savings%2C%20keeping%20the%20big%20picture%20in%20mind%20is%20critical.%20There%20will%20undoubtedly%20be%20boom%20and%20bust%20cycles%20in%20the%20stock%20market%2C%20but%20stay%20invested%2C%20Yoshioka%20said.%20During%20the%20Great%20Financial%20Crisis%2C%20some%20people%20pulled%20their%20money%20out%20of%20the%20market%20to%20protect%20their%20assets%20and%20never%20put%20it%20back%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20don't%20get%20back%20in%2C%20you%20have%20your%20cash%2C%20but%20inflation%20eats%20away%20at%20it%2C%20and%20you%20miss%20out%20on%20a%20lot%20of%20growth%20in%20equity%20markets%2C%26quot%3B%20Yoshioka%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Gen%20Zers%20who%20haven't%20lived%20through%20many%20economic%20cycles%2C%20it's%20important%20not%20to%20panic-sell%20in%20the%20short%20term.%20Equity%20markets%20typically%20bounce%20back%20within%20a%20year%2C%20which%20is%20simply%20a%20blip%20in%20a%20retirement%20portfolio%20that%20could%20span%2050%20to%2060%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2280eb8c54-d39b-43ed-af26-9be03baffb34%5C%22%3EAshley%20Weeks%2C%20wealth%20strategist%20at%20TD%20Bank%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20more%20than%20ever%2C%20a%20successful%20retirement%20depends%20heavily%20on%20personal%20savings%2C%20Weeks%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20retirement%20income%20has%20come%20from%20what%20has%20been%20dubbed%20the%20%26quot%3Bthree-legged%20stool%26quot%3B%20of%20Social%20Security%2C%20pensions%2C%20and%20personal%20savings.%20But%20today%2C%20Weeks%20points%20out%20that%20less%20than%2015%25%20of%20individuals%20in%20the%20private%20sector%20will%20have%20access%20to%20a%20pension%2C%20and%20the%20future%20of%20Social%20Security%20is%20looking%20uncertain%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20that%20the%20burden%20of%20adequate%20retirement%20is%20increasingly%20falling%20on%20the%20individual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Weeks%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Ftarget-date-funds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etarget-date%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20be%20a%20helpful%20tool%20for%20saving%20for%20retirement.%20Many%20company%20401(k)%20plans%20offer%20them%2C%20and%20they%20automatically%20rebalance%20their%20portfolio%20composition%20to%20minimize%20risk%20as%20you%20approach%20retirement.%20A%20target%20date%20fund%20typically%20has%20a%20higher%20allocation%20to%20riskier%20assets%20such%20as%20stocks%20early%20on%20and%20increases%20its%20exposure%20to%20less%20volatile%20fixed%20income%20holdings%20as%20time%20goes%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20approach%20saving%20for%20retirement%20with%20the%20right%20mindset.%20%26quot%3BStart%20saving%20early%20and%20treat%20the%20retirement%20contributions%20just%20like%20a%20monthly%20living%20expense%2C%26quot%3B%20Weeks%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225cb054ca-2549-482b-adb2-655c3ce12c1d%5C%22%3EAlanna%20Morey%2C%20private%20wealth%20advisor%20at%20Ameriprise%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBuilding%20basic%20budgeting%20habits%20is%20key%20to%20retirement%20success%2C%20in%20Morey's%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20one-size-fits-all%20way%20to%20budget%2C%20but%20one%20popular%20strategy%20that%20Morey%20recommends%20is%20the%2050%2F30%2F20%20rule%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20that%2050%25%20of%20after-tax%20income%20goes%20to%20essential%20costs%2C%2030%25%20to%20discretionary%20spending%2C%20and%2020%25%20to%20savings%20or%20other%20financial%20goals%20such%20as%20retirement%20or%20buying%20a%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20before%20saving%20for%20retirement%2C%20Morey%20suggests%20first%20building%20up%20a%20basic%20savings%20fund%20for%20emergencies%20by%20putting%20money%20in%20the%20bank%20or%20a%20high-yield%20savings%20account.%20Once%20you%20have%20enough%20money%20saved%20to%20cover%20a%20few%20months%20of%20essential%20living%20expenses%2C%20then%20it's%20time%20to%20start%20thinking%20about%20contributing%20to%20a%20401(k)%20or%20another%20retirement%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorey%20also%20recommends%20automating%20payments%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%20Credit%20card%20payments%2C%20rent%20payments%2C%20savings%2C%20and%20401(k)%20contributions%20can%20all%20be%20automated%20to%20reduce%20extra%20hassle%20and%20promote%20healthy%20financial%20habits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20possible%2C%20avoid%20credit%20card%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I'm%20paying%2020%25%20interest%20on%20my%20credit%20card%2C%20I'm%20paying%2020%25%20more%20for%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20Morey%20said.%20That%20can%20rapidly%20eat%20into%20your%20ability%20to%20save.%20If%20you%20do%20have%20credit%20card%20debt%2C%20make%20sure%20you%20know%20what%20interest%20rates%20you're%20paying%20and%20have%20a%20plan%20to%20start%20paying%20it%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20change%20those%20habits%20or%20create%20them%20later%20on%2C%20and%20it's%20harder%20to%20catch%20up%20on%20savings%20later%20on%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Morey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-retirement-savings-kickstart-portfolio-investing-tips-managing-money-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729965601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6712a42ca0a0cc14f2225189%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-retirement-savings-kickstart-portfolio-investing-tips-managing-money-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Retirement%20is%20decades%20away%20for%20Gen%20Z%2C%20but%20the%20earlier%20you%20start%20saving%20the%20better.%20Here's%20how%20to%20start%20building%20your%20retirement%20nest%20egg.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22