26quot%3BAfter%20150%20years%2C%20the%20United%20States%20government%20eventually%20stopped%20the%20program%2C%20but%20the%20federal%20government%20has%20never%2C%20never%20formally%20apologised%20for%20what%20happened%20%E2%80%93%20until%20today.%20I%20formally%20apologise%2C%20as%20president%20of%20the%20United%20States%20of%20America%2C%20for%20what%20we%20did.%20I%20formally%20apologise.%20That's%20long%20overdue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHundreds%20of%20native%20Indian%20boarding%20schools%20were%20run%20for%20over%20150%20years%2C%20starting%20from%20the%20early%201800s%20until%20the%20late%201960s.%20The%20federal%20government%20shifted%20thousands%20of%20Native%20American%20children%20from%20their%20homes%20and%20forced%20them%20into%20these%20boarding%20schools%20across%20the%20country.%20The%20idea%20behind%20this%20was%20to%20erase%20the%20tribal%20ties%20and%20cultural%20practices%20of%20these%20children%2C%20The%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F10%2F25%2Fus%2Fus-indian-boarding-schools-history.html%3Fsmid%3Dwhatsapp-nytimes%5C%22%3E%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAt%20these%20schools%2C%20children%20of%20Native%20Americans%20were%20given%20new%20names%2C%20punished%20for%20speaking%20their%20native%20language%2C%20besides%20being%20forcibly%20converted%20to%20Christianity.%20Many%20of%20them%20were%20sexually%20and%20physically%20assaulted%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20July%20this%20year%2C%20the%20US'%20Interior%20Department%20identified%20close%20to%2019%2C000%20such%20children%2C%20who%20attended%20these%20schools%20between%201819%20and%201969.%20However%2C%20it%20acknowledged%20that%20there%20were%20many%20more%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EShockingly%2C%20at%20least%20973%20children%20died%20at%20these%20schools%20and%20were%20buried%20at%2074%20sites%2C%20with%2021%20of%20them%20being%20unmarked%2C%20the%20department's%20report%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThese%20schools%20were%20funded%20by%20Congress%20via%20annual%20appropriations%20and%20by%20selling%20the%20land%20of%20tribes.%20For%20running%20them%2C%20the%20US%20government%20had%20hired%20Roman%20Catholic%2C%20Presbyterian%2C%20Episcopalian%20and%20Congregationalist%20associations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAs%20per%20the%20US%20Interior%20department%2C%20the%20government%20spent%20roughly%20%2423%20billion%20(in%202023%20dollars)%20on%20the%20programme%2C%20operating%20these%20institutions%20in%2037%20states%20and%20territories.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENot%20just%20that%2C%20the%20government%20reportedly%20forced%20parents%20to%20send%20their%20children%20to%20schools%2C%20while%20the%20Interior%20Department%20got%20the%20authority%20to%20withhold%20guaranteed%20food%20rations%20to%20the%20families%20that%20resisted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESome%20of%20the%20survivors%20--%20now%20in%20their%20late%2060s%2C%2070s%20and%2080s%20--%20have%20termed%20their%20experience%20at%20these%20schools%20as%20%26quot%3Bpure%20hell%26quot%3B.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20like%20a%20prison%20setting...%20I%20can%20still%20feel%20the%20hurt%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ron%20Singer%2C%20one%20of%20the%20survivors%2C%20told%20New%20York%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAnother%20person%2C%20named%20Denise%20Lajimodiere%2C%20said%20the%20government's%20policy%20was%20to%20get%20them%20%26quot%3Baway%20from%20their%20homes%2C%20their%20culture%2C%20their%20language%2C%20their%20families%20and%20their%20spirituality%20and%20totally%20assimilate%20them%20into%20white%20ways%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729934640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fqtll5hqc_biden-native-americans_625x300_26_October_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-n